<hint>
<p>One tricky part of setting up the dynamical system is deciding whether it is easier to start with the difference form (such as <m>x_{t+1}-x_t =</m> something) or the function iteration form (such as <m>x_{t+1}=</m> something).  If you choose to start with the difference form, then on the right hand side, you need to put the change in the number of cells.  (And, if the number of cells is doubling, the <em>change</em> is <alert>not</alert> twice the previous number of cells.)  If you choose to start with the function iteration form, then on the right hand side, you need to put an expression that gives the total number of cells after a day.  (And, if the number of cells is doubling, the total number is indeed twice the previous number of cells.)</p>

