<p>Assuming you are convinced that the predicted number is way too large, let's examine where the model went wrong.</p>

<p>The initial rate of cell division per day seems to be <ref uri="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_embryonic_development#Cleavage">in the right ballback</ref>.  So, we're good there.</p>

<p>What does the model assume about the rate of cell division as the pregnancy progresses?  It assumes that the rate of division 
<answer inline='true'>
<choiceinput>
<choice credit='1'>stays constant</choice>
<choice>slow down</choice>
<choice>speeds up</choice>
</choiceinput>
</answer>
